# analytics-service runtime dependencies — SOURCE manifest (tech-debt #7).
#
# This .in file is the human-edited source of DIRECT runtime deps. The
# fully-pinned lock (direct + every transitive) is the generated
# `requirements.txt`, which is what Dockerfile / ci.yml / cassette-refresh /
# Makefile actually install — so prod (Railway) builds are reproducible and a
# new ccxt/transitive can no longer silently change LP-facing money-math
# behavior with zero repo diff (the aiohttp 3.14 incident proved that class).
#
# Regenerate the lock after editing this file:
#   cd analytics-service && make lock        # (uv pip compile --python-version 3.12 --universal)
# CI/prod is Python 3.12 — always compile against 3.12, never the local venv.
#
# Dev/test-only deps (pytest, pyarrow, mypy, …) live in requirements-dev.txt and
# are NOT shipped to prod (Dockerfile installs only requirements.txt).

fastapi==0.138.1
uvicorn[standard]==0.49.0
quantstats==0.0.81
# ccxt parses live broker payloads feeding equity reconstruction + trade
# ingestion; it releases near-daily and the unified API can change behavior
# between releases. Pinned exactly (was `>=4.0`) so a rebuild can't float it.
# 4.5.59 is the version the cassette + equity-reconstruction/funding suites are
# verified green against (tech-debt #7); the code's 4.5.x workarounds
# (equity_reconstruction.py, exchange.py) target this line. To bump: Dependabot
# opens a PR against requirements.txt, then re-run `make lock` and commit the
# regenerated lock (Dependabot's own pip-compile won't match the uv/universal
# format).
ccxt==4.5.61
pandas==2.2.3
numpy==2.5.0
# NOTE: pyarrow is NOT here — it is a TEST-ONLY dependency (pd.read_parquet of the
# golden_252d_input.parquet fixture, tests/conftest.py + tests/fixtures/regen_golden.py).
# It was moved to requirements-dev.txt (H-0537) so the production Railway image (which
# installs ONLY requirements.txt) no longer ships the ~40MB native Arrow wheel and its
# transitive attack surface. pandas 2.2.3 does not require pyarrow at runtime; no
# production code path reads parquet (trades/positions come from Supabase as JSON).
pydantic==2.13.4
python-dotenv==1.2.2
httpx==0.28.1
slowapi==0.1.10
supabase==2.31.0
