# Phase 16 / OBSERV-08: vcrpy pinned for deterministic local-repro of the unified
# key flow. Records 12 cassettes (3 brokers × 4 scenarios) at
# analytics-service/tests/cassettes/ and replays them in CI with NO network
# access. record_mode='once' enforced in tests/conftest_vcr.py — never 'all'.
# Three-layer redaction (filter_headers + filter_query_parameters +
# before_record_response deep walker) covers Bybit v5 / OKX / Binance signing
# variants per Plan 16-08 FIX 3 (Binance signs via QUERY string, not headers).
vcrpy==8.2.1
# aiohttp upper-bound: vcrpy's aiohttp stub (vcr/stubs/aiohttp_stubs.py) imports
# symbols from aiohttp.streams at module load. aiohttp 3.14.0 (released 2026-06)
# removed AsyncStreamReaderMixin, which vcrpy 8.1.1 still referenced — every
# vcr-backed test in test_repro_key_flow.py failed at import with
# `module 'aiohttp.streams' has no attribute 'AsyncStreamReaderMixin'`. vcrpy
# 8.2.1 ships the 3.14-compatible stub (vcrpy#927 resolved), so aiohttp may now
# float to 3.14.x. Cap stays below 3.15 so the next aiohttp minor is gated for
# deliberate review, not a silent transitive float (the 3.14 incident proved
# that class) — supabase->realtime only requires >=3.11.18,<4.0.0.
aiohttp<3.15
